summary:
The Security Council,

Welcoming the Secretary-General's report on the UN operation in Cyprus, 
particularly the call to address the humanitarian issue of missing persons urgently,

Noting the Government of Cyprus's agreement to extend the UN Peacekeeping Force in Cyprus (UNFICYP) due to prevailing conditions,

Welcoming efforts to sensitize peacekeeping personnel on HIV/AIDS and communicable diseases,

1. Reaffirms relevant resolutions on Cyprus, particularly resolution 1251 (1999) and subsequent resolutions;

2. Extends UNFICYP's mandate until 15 June 2001;

3. Requests a report by 1 June 2001 on the implementation of this resolution;

4. Urges the Turkish Cypriot side and Turkish forces to rescind restrictions on UNFICYP operations and restore the military status quo ante at Strovilia;

5. Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
